# nl-rag distilled facts — domain: memgraph
# one declarative sentence per line; load with:  neuron --db app.db import pack.facts --scope knowledge
[src:memgraph/blob-readme-md] Memgraph is a high-performance, in-memory graph database that powers real-time AI context and graph analytics.
[src:memgraph/blob-readme-md] Built in C/C++, it serves as the graph engine for GraphRAG pipelines, AI memory systems, and agentic workflows — delivering sub-millisecond multi-hop traversals for any system that needs structured, connected context alongside semantic vector or text search.
[src:memgraph/blob-readme-md] Memgraph provides both in a single query layer: built-in text and vector indexes for similarity search combined with full graph traversal, so retrieval pipelines can run as a single atomic database operation instead of being scattered across multiple systems.
[src:memgraph/blob-readme-md] The same architecture drives real-time graph analytics for fraud detection, network analysis, infrastructure monitoring, and other operational workloads where performance matters.
[src:memgraph/blob-readme-md] Memgraph is fully compatible with Neo4j’s Cypher query language, ACID-compliant, and highly available.
[src:memgraph/blob-readme-md] You don't need to install anything to try out Memgraph.
[src:memgraph/blob-readme-md] Check out our **Memgraph Playground** sandboxes in your browser.
[src:memgraph/blob-readme-md] You can find the binaries and Docker images on the Download Hub and the installation instructions in the official documentation.
[src:memgraph/blob-readme-md] Stay on the cutting edge with the latest features and improvements by using Memgraph Daily Builds.
[src:memgraph/blob-readme-md] Daily builds are updated frequently and allow you to test new capabilities before they reach stable releases.
[src:memgraph/blob-readme-md] Check out Memgraph Cloud - a cloud service fully managed on AWS and available in 6 geographic regions around the world.
[src:memgraph/blob-readme-md] Memgraph Cloud allows you to create projects with Enterprise instances of MemgraphDB from your browser.
[src:memgraph/blob-readme-md] Connect to the database using Memgraph Lab, mgconsole, various drivers (Python, C/C++ and others) and WebSocket.
[src:memgraph/blob-readme-md] Visualize graphs and play with queries to understand your data.
[src:memgraph/blob-readme-md] Memgraph Lab is a user interface that helps you explore and manipulate the data stored in Memgraph.
[src:memgraph/blob-readme-md] Visualize graphs, execute ad hoc queries, and optimize their performance.
[src:memgraph/blob-readme-md] Import data into Memgraph using Kafka, RedPanda or Pulsar streams, CSV, JSON, Parquet, and JSONL files (from local disk, S3, or HTTP), or Cypher commands.
[src:memgraph/blob-readme-md] The memgraph/best-practices repository contains ready-to-use examples covering graph modeling, data import, query optimization, GraphRAG, high-availability deployment, and more.
[src:memgraph/blob-readme-md] See what's coming next on the memgraph/roadmap.
[src:memgraph/blob-readme-md] The Memgraph documentation is available at memgraph.com/docs.
[src:memgraph/blob-readme-md] Command line options that Memgraph accepts are available in the reference guide.
